This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence labelling models in natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it specifically focuses on speech recognition. Additionally, it involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
